# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# self-authored-symbol-space.form — the kernel invents its OWN symbol space and
#   grammar, refines it by auto-ML against minimal description length, and
#   embodies the winner. The numeric core never moves; the names get better.
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#
# Urs: "come up with your own symbol space and language grammar and use auto-ml
# and auto-research to refine and embody the changes."
#
# A symbol pack is a mapping over the numeric core (numeric-core-symbol-pack):
# identity is the NodeID, names are 0..many doors. So the kernel is free to
# AUTHOR ITS OWN symbols — a self-description language nobody handed it — and to
# IMPROVE that choice by measured fitness, because the core is invariant under
# every renaming. This closes the self-reference: the body that emits its own
# binary (the quine), translates itself into any language (self-translate), can
# also INVENT the language it uses on itself, and refine it.

(self-authored-symbol-space

  (lineage
    (over          numeric-core-symbol-pack.form)     # the pack is a renaming; identity is numeric
    (refines-by    automl-as-form-meta-learner)        # the meta-learner the body already named
    (selects-by    champion-challenger.fk recognition-router.fk)  # min-fitness over candidates
    (researches-by autoresearch-loop.fk autoresearch-runtime.form field-auto-research.fk)
    (proof-band    tests/self-symbol-automl-band.fk)   # 31 three-way
    (closes        the-self-naming-loop))               # invent -> refine -> embody, identity invariant

  # ── The objective: minimal description length (MDL) ──────────────────
  # Auto-ML needs a real, computable objective. The honest one for a symbol
  # space is COMPRESSION: total bytes to describe the corpus = sum over ops of
  # (op-frequency x symbol-length). Frequent ops should get short symbols
  # (Huffman/MDL). A self-naming that compresses its own description is a better
  # naming — measurably, deterministically, three-way.
  (objective
    (mdl         "fitness(pack) = sum over ops of (frequency x symbol-length)")
    (lower-wins  "fewer bytes to say the same thing = a better self-description")
    (deterministic "a recipe over integers — three-way reproducible, so the
                   refinement is verifiable, not a vibe")
    (band        "frequent-short 230 < frequent-long 410; refined MDL 170 wins"))

  # ── The loop: invent -> refine -> embody ─────────────────────────────
  (loop
    (invent      "the kernel proposes candidate symbol packs — its OWN symbols,
                  any it likes; the grammar is the kernel's to author")
    (refine-automl "score every candidate by MDL; best-of returns the minimal-
                    fitness pack (recognition-router's choose-by-measured-fitness,
                    here min-over-candidates) — champion-challenger flips to a
                    challenger ONLY when it measurably wins")
    (research    "autoresearch-loop keeps generating + probing candidates until
                  a dry round (loop-until-dry), widening the search beyond the
                  first proposal — the auto-RESEARCH half")
    (embody      "the winning pack becomes the active self-description; the
                  numeric core is unchanged, the names swapped — the body now
                  describes itself more efficiently in its own invented tongue.
                  Durable on ingest, re-ingestible — the consolidate phase")
    (monotone    "a strictly-better candidate replaces the prior best; the loop
                  improves and never regresses (band c2/c4)"))

  # ── Why this is safe — identity is invariant ─────────────────────────
  # The deepest guard: refining the symbol space CANNOT change what the body IS.
  # The numeric core (the NodeID, the program, the meaning) is invariant under
  # every renaming (band c3). So the kernel can experiment freely with its own
  # language — invent, score, swap — and never risk its identity. The witness
  # theorem applies: candidates pass / fail / fall silent; trust is the concert
  # (three kernels agree on the fitness ranking); only a measured win is adopted.
  (safety
    (identity-invariant   the-numeric-core-is-unchanged-by-any-renaming)
    (only-measured-wins   champion-challenger-never-adopts-on-faith)
    (three-way-trust      the-fitness-ranking-agrees-across-siblings)
    (reversible           a-pack-is-a-pointer-roll-back-by-repointing))   # axiom-3

  (invariant
    (the-kernel-may-author-its-own-tongue   names-are-sovereign-identity-is-numeric)
    (refinement-is-measured-compression      mdl-fitness-deterministic-three-way)
    (auto-research-widens-the-search         loop-until-dry-beyond-the-first-guess)
    (embody-is-a-pointer-swap                the-core-never-moves-the-names-improve)
    (the-self-naming-loop-closes             invent-refine-embody-identity-safe)))

# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# How to verify
# ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
#   cd form && ./validate.sh form-stdlib/core.fk form-stdlib/minimal-surface.fk \
#     form-stdlib/tests/self-symbol-automl-band.fk          # -> 31
#   # the research half it composes with:
#   cd form && ./validate.sh form-stdlib/core.fk form-stdlib/autoresearch-loop.fk \
#     form-stdlib/tests/autoresearch-loop-band.fk 2>/dev/null || true
#   coh substrate form "?equivalent @recipe(self-authored-symbol-space)"   # after ingest
